Math.Equation

Class Token

  • java.lang.Object
    • Math.Equation.Token
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Math.MathObject

    public class Token
extends java.lang.Object
implements Math.MathObject
    A single item from an equation String. Example: "sin(x+2)" yields the tokens {"sin":FUNC, "(":LPAR, "x":VAR, "+":OPER, "2":NUM, ")":RPAR}.
    Since:
    0.1

      • isGroup

        public boolean isGroup()
        Used to determine if a //Node based on a token should be a FinalNode or a Node (in this case, it's the latter). Also used to distinguish between functions / groups and operations.
        Returns:
        True if type is a GROUP or FUNC.

      • isOper

        public boolean isOper()
        Used to distinguish between functions / groups and operations.
        Returns:
        True if type is a OPER.

      • isUni

        public boolean isUni()
        Used to figure out if a node based off this is the "master node".
        Returns:
        True if type == NULL and val == "E".

      • priority

        public int priority()
        Used to figure out which operations come before others in the "order of operations". Parentheses are handeled seperately. if isUni(), priority is 4.

        else if type is FUNC or GROUP, priority is 3.

        else if type is OPER: +,- == 0, *,/ == 1,and ^ == 2.

        else priority is - 1.

        Returns:
        The priority.
